Ok, I guess not :) I don't mind doing it myself but I'm struggling for ideas on how to actually draw the lines. <br />
<br />
I created a LineChart with the following PlotterAreaStyle to test:<br />
<pre><code>&lt;Style x:Key=&quot;LineChartPlotterAreaStyle&quot; TargetType=&quot;charting:PlotterArea&quot; BasedOn=&quot;{StaticResource BasePlotterAreaStyle}&quot;&gt;
        &lt;Setter Property=&quot;Template&quot;&gt;
            &lt;Setter.Value&gt;
                &lt;ControlTemplate TargetType=&quot;charting:PlotterArea&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;charting:FadingListView   
                        x:Name=&quot;itemsPanel&quot; 
                        Style=&quot;{StaticResource FadingListViewStyle}&quot;
                        ItemsSource=&quot;{Binding Path=ParentChart.DataPointGroups, RelativeSource={RelativeSource Mode=TemplatedParent}}&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;charting:FadingListView.ItemsPanel&gt;
                            &lt;ItemsPanelTemplate&gt;
                                &lt;Canvas Margin=&quot;0,10,0,0&quot; /&gt;
                            &lt;/ItemsPanelTemplate&gt;
                        &lt;/charting:FadingListView.ItemsPanel&gt;
                        &lt;charting:FadingListView.ItemTemplate&gt;
                            &lt;DataTemplate&gt;
                                &lt;Polyline Points=&quot;10,100 100,200 200,30 250,200 200,150&quot; Stroke=&quot;Pink&quot; Stretch=&quot;Fill&quot; Width=&quot;Auto&quot; StrokeThickness=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;
                            &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;
                        &lt;/charting:FadingListView.ItemTemplate&gt;
                    &lt;/charting:FadingListView&gt;
                &lt;/ControlTemplate&gt;
            &lt;/Setter.Value&gt;
        &lt;/Setter&gt;
    &lt;/Style&gt;</code></pre>

This gives the polyline correctly but I have no idea on how to correspond this to the data for the series. Anyone have ideas?<br />
